    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2004_Solutions_2004s_page_004_4",
    "text": "B-3 The answer is {a|a > 2}. If a > 2, then the function f(x) = 2a/(a - 2) has the desired property; both perimeter and area of R in this case are 2a7 / (a - 2). Now suppose that a ≤ 2, and let f(x) be a nonnegative continuous function on [0, aj. Let P = (xo, yo) be a point on the graph of f(x) with maximal y-coordinate; then the area of R is at most ayo since it lies below the line y = yo. On the other hand, the points (0,0), (a, 0), and P divide the boundary of R into three sections. The length of the section between (0, 0) and P is at least the distance between (0,0) and P, which is at least yo; the length of the section between P and (a, 0) is similarly at least yo; and the length of the section between (0,0) and (a,0) is a. Since a ≤ 2, we have 2yo + a > ayo and hence the perimeter of R is strictly greater than the area",
